# Platform Feature Implementation Notes

This file documents implemented features by platform, the files used for each feature, and support pages.

## Facebook

### 1) OAuth connect Facebook Pages
- Feature:
	- Builds OAuth URL with page-related scopes.
	- Handles callback, exchanges code to long-lived token, fetches managed pages, stores encrypted page tokens.
- Files used:
	- actions/facebook/auth.ts
	- actions/facebook/callback.ts
	- core/facebook/api.ts
	- app/bridge/callback.v1/auth.facebook/route.ts
	- app/(manage)/accounts/add/page.tsx
- Support pages:
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/facebook-login/
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/pages/access-tokens
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/pages-api/getting-started

### 2) Publish posts to Facebook Page (text/image/video/multi-image + CTA)
- Feature:
	- Publishes text posts.
	- Publishes single image and single video.
	- Publishes multi-image posts via unpublished photo upload + attached_media.
	- Supports optional call_to_action payload.
- Files used:
	- core/facebook/api.ts
	- services/publishing/index.ts
	- actions/content/publish.ts
- Support pages:
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/pages-api/posts
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/graph-api/reference/page/feed
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/graph-api/reference/page/photos
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/graph-api/reference/page/videos

### 3) Sync Page posts into local store
- Feature:
	- Pulls /published_posts with intelligent date windowing.
	- Deduplicates by platformPostId.
	- Stores sync logs and updates lastSyncedAt.
- Files used:
	- actions/facebook/sync-posts.ts
	- core/facebook/api.ts
- Support pages:
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/graph-api/reference/page/published_posts

### 4) Page insights (context-aware)
- Feature:
	- Fetches page insights by metric list.
	- Supports context options: since, until, period, breakdown, metric_type.
	- Returns both summarized aggregates and raw insights payload.
- Files used:
	- actions/facebook/insights.ts
	- core/facebook/api.ts
	- app/(manage)/analytics/page.tsx
	- app/(manage)/accounts/[id]/page.tsx
- Support pages:
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/platforminsights/page/
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/graph-api/reference/insights

### 5) Post-level insights
- Feature:
	- Fetches post_reactions_by_type_total and post_activity_by_action_type.
	- Computes likes/comments/shares summary.
- Files used:
	- actions/facebook/post-insights.ts
	- core/facebook/api.ts
- Support pages:
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/platforminsights/page/#get-metrics-of-a-page-post

### 6) Manage Page capabilities
- Feature:
	- Get page roles/tasks.
	- Get/update page details.
	- Get/update page settings.
	- Get page reviews/ratings.
	- Block a user from page.
	- Accept/reject page change proposal.
- Files used:
	- actions/facebook/manage-page.ts
	- core/facebook/api.ts
- Support pages:
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/pages-api/manage-pages
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/graph-api/reference/page/roles
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/graph-api/reference/page/settings
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/graph-api/reference/page/ratings
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/graph-api/reference/page/blocked

### 7) Webhooks (legacy + dot v1)
- Feature:
	- Legacy webhook endpoint verifies token and processes payload via service layer.
	- Service currently captures proposal/upcoming-change alerts into system alerts.
	- Dot-style endpoints provide token verification + POST acknowledgment for:
		- facebook.page
		- facebook.catalog
		- facebook.user
		- facebook.permissions
		- facebook.application
		- facebook.adaccount
- Files used:
	- app/bridge/webhook.v1/facebook/route.ts
	- services/inbox/facebook.ts
	- app/bridge/webhook.v1/_helpers.ts
	- app/bridge/webhook.v1/facebook.page/route.ts
	- app/bridge/webhook.v1/facebook.catalog/route.ts
	- app/bridge/webhook.v1/facebook.user/route.ts
	- app/bridge/webhook.v1/facebook.permissions/route.ts
	- app/bridge/webhook.v1/facebook.application/route.ts
	- app/bridge/webhook.v1/facebook.adaccount/route.ts
- Support pages:
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/graph-api/webhooks/
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/pages-api/webhooks-for-pages

## Instagram

### 1) OAuth connect Instagram account
- Feature:
	- Builds Instagram OAuth URL.
	- Exchanges code for short-lived token.
	- Exchanges for long-lived token.
	- Fetches profile and stores encrypted token/account mapping.
- Files used:
	- actions/instagram/auth.ts
	- actions/instagram/callback.ts
	- core/instagram/api.ts
	- app/bridge/callback.v1/auth.instagram/route.ts
	- app/(manage)/accounts/add/page.tsx
- Support pages:
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/instagram-basic-display-api
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/instagram-basic-display-api/getting-started
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/instagram-basic-display-api/reference/user

## LinkedIn

### 1) OAuth connect LinkedIn account
- Feature:
	- Builds OAuth URL (openid/profile/w_member_social).
	- Exchanges code for token.
	- Fetches OIDC profile and stores encrypted token/account mapping.
- Files used:
	- actions/linkedin/auth.ts
	- actions/linkedin/callback.ts
	- core/linkedin/api.ts
	- app/bridge/callback.v1/auth.linkedin/route.ts
	- app/(manage)/accounts/add/page.tsx
- Support pages:
	- https://learn.microsoft.com/linkedin/shared/authentication/authorization-code-flow
	- https://learn.microsoft.com/linkedin/consumer/integrations/self-serve/sign-in-with-linkedin

### 2) Publish LinkedIn post
- Feature:
	- Publishes text posts.
	- Supports single-image flow via register upload + binary upload + UGC post.
	- Has fallback to text-only if image upload fails.
- Files used:
	- core/linkedin/api.ts
	- services/publishing/index.ts
	- actions/content/publish.ts
- Support pages:
	- https://learn.microsoft.com/linkedin/consumer/integrations/self-serve/share-on-linkedin
	- https://learn.microsoft.com/linkedin/marketing/community-management/shares/posts-api

### 3) Sync LinkedIn posts into local store
- Feature:
	- Fetches posts by author URN.
	- Deduplicates and stores new posts.
	- Updates account sync timestamps.
- Files used:
	- actions/linkedin/sync-posts.ts
	- core/linkedin/api.ts
- Support pages:
	- https://learn.microsoft.com/linkedin/marketing/community-management/shares/posts-api

## WhatsApp

### 1) Manual account connect (phone number id + access token)
- Feature:
	- Validates account name from WhatsApp API.
	- Encrypts token and stores connected account.
	- Supports token update from account edit page.
- Files used:
	- core/whatsapp/api.ts
	- app/(manage)/accounts/add/page.tsx
	- actions/accounts/index.ts
	- app/(manage)/accounts/[id]/edit/page.tsx
- Support pages:
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/whatsapp/cloud-api
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/whatsapp/cloud-api/reference/phone-numbers

### 2) Inbound webhook processing (messages/calls/account events)
- Feature:
	- Verifies webhook challenge token.
	- Processes message and call events.
	- Creates/updates conversations and stores conversation messages.
	- Stores account alerts/review/settings events in system alerts.
- Files used:
	- app/bridge/webhook.v1/whatsapp/route.ts
	- services/inbox/whatsapp.ts
- Support pages:
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/whatsapp/cloud-api/webhooks
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/whatsapp/cloud-api/reference/messages

### 3) Outbound reply sending
- Feature:
	- Sends WhatsApp text replies through Cloud API using account credentials.
- Files used:
	- actions/inbox/sender.ts
	- core/whatsapp/api.ts
- Support pages:
	- https://developers.facebook.com/docs/whatsapp/cloud-api/reference/messages

## Twitter (current state)

### 1) Manual placeholder connect only
- Feature:
	- UI allows entering username/password and stores account metadata.
	- No official Twitter/X API integration for publish/sync/webhook in current code.
- Files used:
	- app/(manage)/accounts/add/page.tsx
	- actions/db.ts
- Support pages:
	- https://developer.x.com/en/docs

## Cross-platform shared features

### 1) Unified multi-account publishing orchestrator
- Feature:
	- Publishes one post collection to selected Facebook and LinkedIn accounts.
	- Stores per-platform post records and updates collection status.
- Files used:
	- services/publishing/index.ts
	- actions/content/publish.ts
	- core/facebook/api.ts
	- core/linkedin/api.ts

### 2) Account management
- Feature:
	- Disconnect account.
	- Update WhatsApp token.
- Files used:
	- actions/accounts/index.ts
	- app/(manage)/accounts/page.tsx
	- app/(manage)/accounts/[id]/edit/page.tsx

### 3) API bridge base endpoint
- Feature:
	- Health/info response for bridge root.
- Files used:
	- app/bridge/api.v1/route.ts

